Learning GIT (Version Control System) [Day 4] ðŸš€

Let's learn about the Starting A Project, Temporary Commits, Tracking Path Changes & Help Commands ðŸ‘‡

âœ… Starting A Project

â—½ $ git clone [project url] --> Downloads a project with the entire history from the remote repository

â—½ $ git fetch [remote] --> Fetch changes from the remote, but do not update tracking branches

â—½ $ git rebase [branch] --> apply any commits of the current branch ahead of the specified one

âœ… Temporary Commits

â—½ $ git stash --> Put current changes in your working directory into the stash for later use.

â—½ $ git stash list --> list stack-order of stashed file changes

â—½ $ git stash pop Apply --> stored stash content into the working directory, and clear stash.

â—½ $ git stash drop --> Delete a specific stash from all your previous stashes.

âœ… TRACKING PATH CHANGES

Versioning file removes and path changes

â—½ $ git rm [file] --> Remove the file from the working directory and staging area.

â—½ $ git mv [existing-path] [new-path] --> change an existing file path and stage the move

â—½ $ git log --stat -M --> show all commit logs with an indication of any paths that move

âœ… HELP

â—½ $ git help --> Display help information about Git

â—½ $ git (Command) help --> Display help information about Git Command
